# Test file that mimics crontab.
#
# Sensors indicate no shuttle or other ships in this sector. According to
# coordinates, we have traveled 7,000 light years and are located near the
# system J-25. Tractor beam released, sir.
#
# Force field maintaining our hull integrity. Damage report? Sections 27, 28
# and 29 on decks four, five and six destroyed. Without our shields, at this
# range it is probable a photon detonation could destroy the Enterprise.
#
# For more information see http://github.com/ross-spencer/cronical
#
# Long-form:
#
# minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week command
#
# Short-form:
#
# m h dom mon dow command

# Run a command at 16:10 and 16:15 every day.
# Generates 8 cron tasks.
10,15 20,16 1,20 * * echo "test one (8 tasks)"

# This runs a command at 2:00 AM PDT/PST on Friday and Saturday.
# Generates 2 cron tasks.
0 2 * * 5,6 echo "test two (2 tasks)"

# This runs at midnight on New Years Day (January 1st).
# Generates 1 cron task.
0 0 1 1 * echo "test three happy new year! (1 task)"

# Top of every hour.
# Generates 1 cron task.
0 * * * * echo "test four (1 task)"

# Every 15 minutes.
# Generates 1 cron task.
*/15 * * * * echo "test five (1 task)"

# Deliberately broken.
# Generates 0 cron tasks.
0 Ï€ * * * echo "test six (1 task / 1 invalid)"

# Every 30 minutes.
# Generates 1 cron task.
*/30 * * * * echo "test seven (1 task)"

# Every 10 minutes.
# Generates 1 cron task.
*/10 * * * * echo "test eight (1 task)"

# At midnight, 2am, and 4am
# Generates 3 cron tasks.
* 0,2,4 * * * echo "test nine (3 tasks)"

# Every 1 hour.
# Generates 1 cron task.
* */1 * * * echo "test ten (1 task)"

# Run Jan, Feb 31, and Aug 31. Feb 30/31 should fail. Jan/Aug 31 shouldn't.
# Generates 6 cron task.
* * 30,31 2,8,1 * echo "test eleven (6 tasks / 2 invalid)"

# 10th minute of every hour in October.
# Generates 1 cron task.
10 * * 10 * echo "test twelve (1 tasks)"

# Null.
# Generates 0 cron task.
* * * * * echo "test thirteen (0 tasks / cron is null)"

# This runs at midnight on New Years Day (January 1st). If it's a Monday.
# Generates 1 cron task.
0 0 1 JAN MON echo "test fourteen happy new year! (1 task)"

# This runs at midnight on New Years Day (January 1st). If it's a Sunday.
# Generates 1 cron task.
0 0 1 1 SUN echo "test fifteen happy new year! (1 task)"
